						<summary>

						<p>Chōḻa, Rājarāja II, 8th year = A.D. 1154.</p>						

						<p>This states that the <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> lands of the temples were lying waste for want of tenants and that a Śivabrāhmaṇa came forward to purchase some piece of land for cultivating it under <hi rend="italic">kuḍinīṅgā-dēvadāna</hi> tenure and measure out some specified quantity of paddy to the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
